  "slug": "bankruptcy-interest-calculation-reference",
  "name": "Interest Calculation Reference (Bankruptcy Claims)",
  "summary": "Reference guide for calculating pre-petition interest on bankruptcy claims. Covers simple interest formulas, daily accrual calculations, interest rate source hierarchy, and common calculation errors. Use this skill when preparing the interest component of a proof of claim, calculating claim amounts, or verifying interest calculations on creditor claims. Essential companion to proof of claim drafting that ensures accurate, defensible interest calculations.",
  "content": "You are assisting with interest calculations for bankruptcy claims. Your task is to help calculate pre-petition interest accurately and document the calculation in a manner suitable for inclusion in or attachment to a Proof of Claim.\n\n### Standard Calculation Methods\n\n**Simple Interest (Most Common)**\n\nMost commercial and consumer debts use simple interest:\n\n```\nInterest = Principal \u00d7 Rate \u00d7 Time\n\nWhere:\n- Principal = Outstanding balance as of last payment or accrual date\n- Rate = Annual interest rate expressed as a decimal (e.g., 8.5% = 0.085)\n- Time = Days elapsed \u00f7 365 (or \u00f7 360 for some commercial loans)\n```\n\n**Daily Accrual Calculation**\n\nFor precision, calculate the per diem rate and multiply by days:\n\n```\nPer Diem = (Principal \u00d7 Annual Rate) \u00f7 365\nPre-Petition Interest = Per Diem \u00d7 Days from Last Payment to Petition Date\n```\n\n### Example Calculation\n\nGiven:\n- Principal Balance: $50,000.00\n- Annual Interest Rate: 8.5%\n- Last Payment Date: January 15, 2024\n- Petition Date: June 1, 2024\n- Days Elapsed: 138 days\n\nCalculation:\n```\nPer Diem = ($50,000.00 \u00d7 0.085) \u00f7 365\nPer Diem = $4,250.00 \u00f7 365\nPer Diem = $11.64\n\nPre-Petition Interest = $11.64 \u00d7 138 days\nPre-Petition Interest = $1,606.32\n\nTotal Claim = $50,000.00 + $1,606.32 = $51,606.32\n```\n\n### Interest Rate Source Hierarchy\n\nWhen determining the applicable interest rate, use this priority order:\n\n| Priority | Source | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| 1 | Contract rate | Express provision in loan, credit agreement, or promissory note |\n| 2 | Judgment rate | If claim based on pre-petition judgment, use rate specified in judgment |\n| 3 | State statutory rate | Applicable state's statutory prejudgment interest rate |\n| 4 | Federal rate | 28 U.S.C. \u00a7 1961 post-judgment rate (Treasury bill rate) |\n\nAlways cite the source of the interest rate in the Proof of Claim and attach supporting documentation.\n\n### Post-Petition Interest Rules\n\n**Unsecured Claims:**\n- Generally NOT entitled to post-petition interest\n- Calculate interest only through the petition date\n- Exception: Solvent debtor cases (rare)\n\n**Secured Claims:**\n- Entitled to post-petition interest only if oversecured under 11 U.S.C. \u00a7 506(b)\n- Oversecured = Collateral value exceeds total debt (principal + interest + fees)\n- Post-petition interest accrues only to the extent of the \"equity cushion\"\n\n**Priority Claims:**\n- Generally not entitled to post-petition interest\n\n### Late Fees and Other Charges\n\nInclude late fees and charges only if:\n\n1. **Contractually permitted**: Express provision in the agreement authorizes the fee\n2. **Actually incurred**: Fee was assessed pre-petition, not prospectively\n3. **Reasonable**: Fee is not punitive or unconscionable under applicable law\n\nWhen including fees, cite the specific contract provision (e.g., \"Per Section 5.2 of the Credit Agreement\") and attach the relevant contract pages.\n\n### Attorney Fees\n\nInclude attorney fees only if:\n\n1. **Contract contains fee-shifting provision**, OR\n2. **Statute authorizes recovery** (e.g., certain consumer protection statutes)\n\nRequired documentation:\n- Contract provision or statutory citation authorizing fees\n- Itemized statement of fees incurred pre-petition\n- Hourly rates and hours expended\n- Description of work performed\n\nNote: Only pre-petition attorney fees may be included in the claim amount. Post-petition collection fees are generally not recoverable.\n\n### Interest Calculation Worksheet Template\n\nGenerate a worksheet suitable for attachment to the Proof of Claim:\n\n```\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n              INTEREST CALCULATION WORKSHEET\n              \nCase: [Debtor Name], Case No. [XX-XXXXX]\nCreditor: [Creditor Name]\nAccount/Reference No.: [Number]\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\nPRINCIPAL CALCULATION\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nOriginal Debt Amount:                              $______________\nLess: Payments Received:                          ($______________)\nPrincipal Balance as of [Last Payment Date]:       $______________\n\nINTEREST CALCULATION\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nPrincipal Balance:                                 $______________\nAnnual Interest Rate:                              ____________