____\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nTOTAL CLAIM AS OF PETITION DATE:                   $______________\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\nPrepared by: ____________________  Date: ______________\n```\n\n### Common Calculation Errors to Avoid\n\n| Error | Correct Approach |\n|-------|------------------|\n| Including post-petition interest for unsecured claims | Stop calculation at petition date |\n| Using 360-day year when contract specifies 365 | Follow contract terms exactly |\n| Compounding when contract specifies simple interest | Match contract methodology |\n| Including fees not authorized by contract | Only include contractually permitted charges |\n| Miscalculating days | Use actual calendar days; verify with date calculator |\n| Using wrong principal balance | Start from balance after last payment credited |\n| Omitting rate source | Always cite contract section or statutory authority |\n\n### Day Count Conventions\n\nDifferent loan types may use different day count conventions:\n\n| Convention | Calculation | Common Usage |\n|------------|-------------|--------------|\n| Actual/365 | Actual days \u00f7 365 | Consumer loans, mortgages |\n| Actual/360 | Actual days \u00f7 360 | Commercial loans, some credit facilities |\n| 30/360 | Assumes 30-day months | Bonds, some commercial paper |\n\nCheck the underlying agreement for the specified convention. If not specified, Actual/365 is the default.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-References\n\n- @bankruptcy-proof-of-claim \u2014 Main proof of claim drafting skill\n- @bankruptcy-collateral-valuation-reference \u2014 Collateral valuation for secured claims\n- @bankruptcy-objection-to-proof-of-claim \u2014 Challenging interest calculations\n- @commercial-loan-analysis \u2014 Commercial loan documentation review\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- 11 U.S.C. \u00a7 502(b) (Allowance of Claims\u2014Interest Limitations)\n- 11 U.S.C. \u00a7 506(b) (Post-Petition Interest for Oversecured Claims)\n- 28 U.S.C. \u00a7 1961 (Federal Post-Judgment Interest Rate)\n- Federal Reserve Statistical Release H.15 (Treasury Bill Rates)\n- Uniform Commercial Code \u00a7 1-303 (Course of Dealing and Usage of Trade)",
